+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016fM9iCSML9BC12FR5mLM8p","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me implement the solution. The key insight from the error stratagem: this is linear algebra over finite fields.\n\nFor `solveToggle`: System of linear equations over GF(2). Build augmented matrix, Gaussian eliminate, find particular solution + null space, enumerate free variables (up to 2^k where k = # free vars, but k should be small for well-formed puzzles, and we can optimize).\n\nFor `solveCounter`: Same but over GF(p) where p is prime.\n\nFor optimization with free variables: we need minimum total presses, then lexicographically smallest. With up to 40 buttons and potentially many free variables, we need to be smart. But given the 5-second constraint and up to 40 variables, worst case free variables could be up to 40 (if no lights). We need to handle this carefully.\n\nLet me think about the optimization approach:\n- For GF(2) (toggle): each free variable is 0 or 1. We want minimum number of 1s (fewest buttons), then lex smallest. With up to 40 free variables, 2^40 is too many. But we can use a different approach: for each possible count of presses (0, 1, 2, ...), find the lex smallest combination of free variable assignments.\n- Actually, since setting a free variable changes the dependent variables deterministically, we need to evaluate the full solution for each free variable assignment, count total presses, and find minimum then lex smallest.\n- For up to ~20 free variables, we could enumerate (2^20 = ~1M). For more, we'd need a smarter approach.\n\nLet me think more carefully. In practice, for 40 lights and 40 buttons, the rank is typically close to min(40,40)=40, so few free variables. But we need to handle the worst case.\n\nFor the GF(2) case with many free variables: We want to minimize the Hamming weight of the solution vector. This is the \"minimum weight codeword\" problem, which is NP-hard in general. But for up to 40 variables, with the constraint that we need to finish in 5 seconds, we can use meet-in-the-middle for up to ~40 free variables (split into two halves of 20 each).\n\nActually, let me reconsider. The problem says up to 40 buttons and 40 lights. The number of free variables = 40 - rank. The rank is at most min(40, 40) = 40 but also at most the number of lights = 40. So free variables could theoretically be 0 to 40. But in practice, if there are 40 independent constraints, there are 0 free variables.\n\nFor robustness, let me implement meet-in-the-middle for the optimization step when free variables exceed some threshold, and direct enumeration otherwise."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":285,"cache_read_input_tokens":23257,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":285},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6e4a8a91-ca00-4427-b1dd-9719dbe40568","uuid":"5efda14c-8e74-49b5-b3ae-12e6a6db63a7"}
+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_016fM9iCSML9BC12FR5mLM8p","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_016qnFC1bTcxBNaQ61Fhxm6e","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/workspace/src/index.ts","content":"/**\n * Factory Reset — Toggle and Counter puzzle solvers\n *\n * Both puzzles reduce to systems of linear equations over finite fields:\n * - Toggle: GF(2) (XOR)\n * - Counter: GF(p) for prime p\n *\n * We use Gaussian elimination to find particular solutions and null spaces,\n * then optimize over free variables for minimum presses / lex smallest.\n */\n\ninterface Machine {\n  target: boolean[];\n  buttons: number[][];\n}\n\n// --- Finite field arithmetic helpers ---\n\nfunction mod(a: number, p: number): number {\n  return ((a % p) + p) % p;\n}\n\nfunction modInverse(a: number, p: number): number {\n  // Extended Euclidean algorithm for modular inverse in GF(p)\n  a = mod(a, p);\n  if (a === 0) return 0;\n  let [old_r, r] = [a, p];\n  let [old_s, s] = [1, 0];\n  while (r !== 0) {\n    const q = Math.floor(old_r / r);\n    [old_r, r] = [r, old_r - q * r];\n    [old_s, s] = [s, old_s - q * s];\n  }\n  return mod(old_s, p);\n}\n\n// --- Gaussian elimination over GF(p) ---\n\ninterface GaussResult {\n  /** Rank of the matrix */\n  rank: number;\n  /** Whether a solution exists */\n  solvable: boolean;\n  /** Particular solution (one valid assignment for each button) */\n  particular: number[];\n  /** Null space basis vectors (each vector is length numButtons) */\n  nullSpace: number[][];\n  /** Pivot columns (button indices that are determined) */\n  pivotCols: number[];\n  /** Free columns (button indices that are free) */\n  freeCols: number[];\n}\n\nfunction gaussianElimination(\n  matrix: number[][],\n  rhs: number[],\n  numButtons: number,\n  numLights: number,\n  p: number\n): GaussResult {\n  // Build augmented matrix [A | b] where A[i][j] = how many times button j affects light i\n  const aug: number[][] = [];\n  for (let i = 0; i < numLights; i++) {\n    const row = new Array(numButtons + 1);\n    for (let j = 0; j < numButtons; j++) {\n      row[j] = mod(matrix[i][j], p);\n    }\n    row[numButtons] = mod(rhs[i], p);\n    aug.push(row);\n  }\n\n  const pivotCols: number[] = [];\n  let pivotRow = 0;\n\n  // Forward elimination\n  for (let col = 0; col < numButtons && pivotRow < numLights; col++) {\n    // Find pivot\n    let maxRow = -1;\n    for (let row = pivotRow; row < numLights; row++) {\n      if (aug[row][col] !== 0) {\n        maxRow = row;\n        break;\n      }\n    }\n    if (maxRow === -1) continue; // No pivot in this column, it's a free variable\n\n    // Swap rows\n    [aug[pivotRow], aug[maxRow]] = [aug[maxRow], aug[pivotRow]];\n\n    // Scale pivot row so pivot element = 1\n    const inv = modInverse(aug[pivotRow][col], p);\n    for (let j = col; j <= numButtons; j++) {\n      aug[pivotRow][j] = mod(aug[pivotRow][j] * inv, p);\n    }\n\n    // Eliminate column in all other rows\n    for (let row = 0; row < numLights; row++) {\n      if (row === pivotRow || aug[row][col] === 0) continue;\n      const factor = aug[row][col];\n      for (let j = col; j <= numButtons; j++) {\n        aug[row][j] = mod(aug[row][j] - factor * aug[pivotRow][j], p);\n      }\n    }\n\n    pivotCols.push(col);\n    pivotRow++;\n  }\n\n  const rank = pivotCols.length;\n\n  // Check consistency: any row with all-zero coefficients but non-zero RHS\n  for (let row = rank; row < numLights; row++) {\n    if (aug[row][numButtons] !== 0) {\n      return {\n        rank,\n        solvable: false,\n        particular: [],\n        nullSpace: [],\n        pivotCols,\n        freeCols: [],\n      };\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Identify free columns\n  const pivotSet = new Set(pivotCols);\n  const freeCols: number[] = [];\n  for (let j = 0; j < numButtons; j++) {\n    if (!pivotSet.has(j)) freeCols.push(j);\n  }\n\n  // Extract particular solution (set all free variables to 0)\n  const particular = new Array(numButtons).fill(0);\n  for (let i = 0; i < rank; i++) {\n    particular[pivotCols[i]] = aug[i][numButtons];\n  }\n\n  // Extract null space basis vectors\n  // For each free variable, set it to 1, others to 0, solve for pivot variables\n  const nullSpace: number[][] = [];\n  for (const freeCol of freeCols) {\n    const vec = new Array(numButtons).fill(0);\n    vec[freeCol] = 1;\n    for (let i = 0; i < rank; i++) {\n      // pivot variable i = -aug[i][freeCol] (since in RREF)\n      vec[pivotCols[i]] = mod(-aug[i][freeCol], p);\n    }\n    nullSpace.push(vec);\n  }\n\n  return { rank, solvable: true, particular, nullSpace, pivotCols, freeCols };\n}\n\n// --- Optimizing over free variables ---\n\n/**\n * Given a particular solution and null space basis, find the solution\n * with minimum total presses (sum of values), breaking ties lexicographically.\n * Values are in range [0, p-1].\n */\nfunction optimizeSolution(\n  particular: number[],\n  nullSpace: number[][],\n  p: number\n): number[] | null {\n  const numButtons = particular.length;\n  const numFree = nullSpace.length;\n\n  if (numFree === 0) {\n    return particular.map((v) => mod(v, p));\n  }\n\n  // For small number of free variables, enumerate all p^numFree combinations\n  // For p=2 and numFree <= 25: 2^25 = 33M (might be tight but doable)\n  // For larger cases, use meet-in-the-middle\n\n  const totalCombinations = Math.pow(p, numFree);\n\n  if (totalCombinations <= 5_000_000) {\n    return enumerateOptimal(particular, nullSpace, p);\n  } else {\n    return meetInTheMiddleOptimal(particular, nullSpace, p);\n  }\n}\n\nfunction computeSolution(\n  particular: number[],\n  nullSpace: number[][],\n  coeffs: number[],\n  p: number\n): number[] {\n  const n = particular.length;\n  const result = new Array(n);\n  for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n    let val = particular[i];\n    for (let k = 0; k < coeffs.length; k++) {\n      val += coeffs[k] * nullSpace[k][i];\n    }\n    result[i] = mod(val, p);\n  }\n  return result;\n}\n\nfunction solutionSum(sol: number[]): number {\n  let s = 0;\n  for (let i = 0; i < sol.length; i++) s += sol[i];\n  return s;\n}\n\nfunction lexCompare(a: number[], b: number[]): number {\n  for (let i = 0; i < a.length; i++) {\n    if (a[i] < b[i]) return -1;\n    if (a[i] > b[i]) return 1;\n  }\n  return 0;\n}\n\nfunction enumerateOptimal(\n  particular: number[],\n  nullSpace: number[][],\n  p: number\n): number[] {\n  const numFree = nullSpace.length;\n  const coeffs = new Array(numFree).fill(0);\n\n  let bestSol: number[] | null = null;\n  let bestSum = Infinity;\n\n  const enumerate = (idx: number): void => {\n    if (idx === numFree) {\n      const sol = computeSolution(particular, nullSpace, coeffs, p);\n      const s = solutionSum(sol);\n      if (s < bestSum || (s === bestSum && lexCompare(sol, bestSol!) < 0)) {\n        bestSum = s;\n        bestSol = sol;\n      }\n      return;\n    }\n    for (let v = 0; v < p; v++) {\n      coeffs[idx] = v;\n      enumerate(idx + 1);\n    }\n  };\n\n  enumerate(0);\n  return bestSol!;\n}\n\nfunction meetInTheMiddleOptimal(\n  particular: number[],\n  nullSpace: number[][],\n  p: number\n): number[] {\n  const numFree = nullSpace.length;\n  const numButtons = particular.length;\n\n  // Split free variables into two halves\n  const halfA = Math.floor(numFree / 2);\n  const halfB = numFree - halfA;\n\n  // For each half, compute the \"delta\" each combination adds to the particular solution\n  // Then for the full solution = particular + deltaA + deltaB,\n  // we want to minimize sum and lex order.\n\n  // Precompute all combinations for the first half\n  type HalfEntry = { delta: number[]; sum: number; coeffs: number[] };\n\n  function generateHalf(startIdx: number, count: number): HalfEntry[] {\n    const entries: HalfEntry[] = [];\n    const coeffs = new Array(count).fill(0);\n    const totalCombs = Math.pow(p, count);\n\n    for (let c = 0; c < totalCombs; c++) {\n      // Decode c into coefficients\n      let tmp = c;\n      for (let i = count - 1; i >= 0; i--) {\n        coeffs[i] = tmp % p;\n        tmp = Math.floor(tmp / p);\n      }\n\n      // Compute delta for these coefficients\n      const delta = new Array(numButtons).fill(0);\n      for (let k = 0; k < count; k++) {\n        if (coeffs[k] === 0) continue;\n        const basisIdx = startIdx + k;\n        for (let j = 0; j < numButtons; j++) {\n          delta[j] += coeffs[k] * nullSpace[basisIdx][j];\n        }\n      }\n\n      // We don't mod here yet; we'll mod when combining\n      entries.push({\n        delta: delta.slice(),\n        sum: 0, // Will compute when combining\n        coeffs: coeffs.slice(),\n      });\n    }\n\n    return entries;\n  }\n\n  const entriesA = generateHalf(0, halfA);\n  const entriesB = generateHalf(halfA, halfB);\n\n  let bestSol: number[] | null = null;\n  let bestSum = Infinity;\n\n  // For each combination of A and B, compute full solution\n  for (const a of entriesA) {\n    for (const b of entriesB) {\n      const sol = new Array(numButtons);\n      let s = 0;\n      for (let j = 0; j < numButtons; j++) {\n        sol[j] = mod(particular[j] + a.delta[j] + b.delta[j], p);\n        s += sol[j];\n      }\n      if (s < bestSum || (s === bestSum && lexCompare(sol, bestSol!) < 0)) {\n        bestSum = s;\n        bestSol = sol;\n      }\n    }\n  }\n\n  return bestSol!;\n}\n\n// --- Public API ---\n\nexport function solveToggle(machine: Machine): number[] | null {\n  const { target, buttons } = machine;\n  const numLights = target.length;\n  const numButtons = buttons.length;\n\n  // Build coefficient matrix: matrix[light][button] = 1 if button toggles light\n  const matrix: number[][] = [];\n  for (let i = 0; i < numLights; i++) {\n    matrix.push(new Array(numButtons).fill(0));\n  }\n  for (let j = 0; j < numButtons; j++) {\n    for (const light of buttons[j]) {\n      matrix[light][j] = 1;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // RHS: target configuration (true=1, false=0)\n  const rhs = target.map((t) => (t ? 1 : 0));\n\n  const result = gaussianElimination(matrix, rhs, numButtons, numLights, 2);\n\n  if (!result.solvable) return null;\n\n  const optimal = optimizeSolution(result.particular, result.nullSpace, 2);\n  if (!optimal) return null;\n\n  // Convert to sorted button indices (those pressed = 1)\n  const pressed: number[] = [];\n  for (let i = 0; i < numButtons; i++) {\n    if (optimal[i] === 1) pressed.push(i);\n  }\n\n  return pressed;\n}\n\nexport function solveCounter(\n  lights: number[],\n  buttons: number[][],\n  modulus: number\n): number[] | null {\n  const numLights = lights.length;\n  const numButtons = buttons.length;\n\n  // Build coefficient matrix: matrix[light][button] = 1 if button affects light\n  const matrix: number[][] = [];\n  for (let i = 0; i < numLights; i++) {\n    matrix.push(new Array(numButtons).fill(0));\n  }\n  for (let j = 0; j < numButtons; j++) {\n    for (const light of buttons[j]) {\n      matrix[light][j] = 1;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // RHS: target counter values\n  const rhs = lights.map((v) => mod(v, modulus));\n\n  const result = gaussianElimination(\n    matrix,\n    rhs,\n    numButtons,\n    numLights,\n    modulus\n  );\n\n  if (!result.solvable) return null;\n\n  const optimal = optimizeSolution(\n    result.particular,\n    result.nullSpace,\n    modulus\n  );\n  if (!optimal) return null;\n\n  return optimal;\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":285,"cache_read_input_tokens":23257,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":285},"output_tokens":6,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6e4a8a91-ca00-4427-b1dd-9719dbe40568","uuid":"7862651f-ac2d-471d-b121-844240e44e58"}
